        {
          "role": "assistant",
          "content": "Under the Bharatiya Nagarik Suraksha Sanhita (BNSS), here is the step-by-step procedure to file a First Information Report (FIR) or complaint:\n\n* **Lodge Information:** You can report a cognizable crime orally or in writing to the officer-in-charge of any police station (Section 173 BNSS).\n* **Zero FIR:** You can file a Zero FIR at any police station, regardless of where the crime occurred. They must register it and transfer it to the jurisdictional station.\n* **E-FIR/Online Registration:** BNSS allows filing complaints electronically (e-FIR), which must be signed/verified by the complainant within 3 days.\n* **Free Copy:** The police must provide a copy of the registered FIR to you free of cost immediately.\n* **If Police Refuse:** If the station officer refuses to register your FIR, you can send the substance of the information in writing to the Superintendent of Police (SP) or lodge a private complaint before a Judicial Magistrate.\n\n*Disclaimer: This information is for educational purposes and does not constitute formal legal advice.*",
